WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:01:17.880 align:middle line:90%


00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:21.250 align:middle line:84%
>> There is a pilgrimage of
epic proportions that occurs

00:01:21.250 --> 00:01:24.400 align:middle line:84%
at the banks of the three
holiest rivers in India--

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:29.650 align:middle line:84%
the Ganges, the Yamuna,
and the mythical Saraswati.

00:01:29.650 --> 00:01:34.240 align:middle line:84%
That gathering is
called Kumbh Mela.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:36.160 align:middle line:84%
Untold millions of
devoted individuals

00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:40.617 align:middle line:84%
made this journey in 2013,
each on their own pilgrimage,

00:01:40.617 --> 00:01:41.700 align:middle line:90%
each for their own reason.

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:44.950 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.950 --> 00:01:46.360 align:middle line:84%
Most come on the
faith and belief

00:01:46.360 --> 00:01:48.490 align:middle line:84%
that they'll break the
cycle of reincarnation

00:01:48.490 --> 00:01:51.190 align:middle line:84%
and be granted access
to the afterlife.

00:01:51.190 --> 00:01:56.260 align:middle line:84%
Others come for resolution,
for love, community, devotion,

00:01:56.260 --> 00:01:57.650 align:middle line:90%
and even curiosity.

00:01:57.650 --> 00:02:01.180 align:middle line:90%


00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:04.310 align:middle line:84%
But no matter what, each
person makes the journey

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:06.840 align:middle line:84%
to connect with something
greater than themselves.

00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:09.840 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

