00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:14.410 align:middle line:10%
As a photographer, my
work and my purpose

00:02:14.410 --> 00:02:17.990 align:middle line:10%
is about reminding us of
the connection and the unity

00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:20.090 align:middle line:10%
that we already have
with the divine.

00:02:20.090 --> 00:02:27.610 align:middle line:90%


00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:30.400 align:middle line:10%
Here, three men from three
completely different worlds

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.280 align:middle line:10%
converge at the confluence
of these rivers.

00:02:33.280 --> 00:02:36.850 align:middle line:10%
One in the name of purpose,
one in the name of faith,

00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:38.290 align:middle line:10%
and one in the name of devotion.

00:02:38.290 --> 00:02:49.650 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:53.330 align:middle line:84%
The water represents all
of these things and more.

00:02:53.330 --> 00:02:56.130 align:middle line:90%
The Yamuna, depth and clarity.

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:59.160 align:middle line:84%
